	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Many mapper 7 games on the <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/AxROM" class="postlink">ANROM or AOROM board</a> fall into &quot;Requires CPU's value to prevail over the ROM's value&quot; because they expect the PRG ROM to disable itself during writes. ANROM decodes PRG ROM with 74HC02, and AOROM uses a PRG ROM whose +CE is wired to CPU R/W.</div><br /><br />Those games should be in a fourth category, Board's Hardware ensures that the CPU's value prevails over the ROM's value.  That would describe every board that disables ROM on a CPU write.

		

